oc nations attempting to moderate UAR criticism of Qasim.\nUSSR delivers three motor torpedo boats to Iraq.\n\nII. ASIA-AFRICA\nYemen--Troops sent against dissident tribes complain pay is in arrears.\nIsrael--Ben-Gurion forms new government; offers Arabs nonaggression pacts.\nMorocco--Uneasy relations between King and leftist government placed under new strain.\nBrussels offers to accelerate progress toward self-government for Congo.\nNepal plans to establish diplomatic relations with Czechoslovakia.\nSouth Korea may be planning seizure of Japanese fishing boats as reprisal for Japanese - North Korean repatriation.\n\nIII. THE WEST\nHaitian cabinet resigns", "token_count": 100, "token_end_0based": 99, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "18 december 1959 i the communist bloc ussr and bloc nations attempting to moderate uar criticism of qasim ussr delivers three motor torpedo boats to iraq ii asia-africa yemen troops sent against dissident tribes complain pay is in arrears israel ben-gurion forms new government offers arabs nonaggression pacts morocco uneasy relations between king and leftist government placed under new strain brussels offers to accelerate progress toward self-government for congo nepal plans to establish diplomatic relations with czechoslovakia south korea may be planning seizure of japanese fishing boats as reprisal for japanese north korean repatriation iii the west haitian cabinet resigns", "unred_source_page": 3}
